<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Challenge 4: File Access</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <a href="/dashboard"><< Back to Hub</a>
        <h1>Challenge 4: Path Traversal</h1>
        <div class="card">
            <p>This internal tool allows employees to download the BBQ menu.</p>
            <p>The developer used a very naive way to serve files. Can you manipulate the request to read <code>secret_bbq_recipe.txt</code> located in the parent directory?</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h3>Download Files</h3>
            <p><a href="/download?file=menu.txt" target="_blank">[ Download Menu ]</a></p>
            
            <form action="/download" method="GET" target="_blank">
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="file">Manual file request:</label>
                    <input type="text" id="file" name="file" value="menu.txt">
                </div>
                <button type="submit">Fetch File</button>
            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
